<TITLE>im2bw</TITLE>
<TYPE>SIVP Toolbox</TYPE>
<DATE>April, 2006</DATE>
<SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="im2bw">Convert image to binary</SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
<CALLING_SEQUENCE>
   <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>im2 = im2bw(im, thresh)</CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
</CALLING_SEQUENCE>
<PARAM>
<PARAM_INDENT>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>im</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
     An matrix/image, which can be ANY image supported by SIVP.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>thresh</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
     Threshold value. You specify <TT>thresh</TT> in the range [0,1], regardless of the class of the input image.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>im2</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
     Boolean matrix.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
</PARAM_INDENT>
</PARAM>
<DESCRIPTION>
<P>
<TT>im2bw</TT> convert intensity or RGB images to binary images. The output is a boolean matrix, which has value of <TT>%T</TT> for all pixels in the input image with luminance grater than <TT>thresh</TT> and <TT>%F</TT> for all the other pixels. (You specify <TT>thresh</TT> in the range [0,1], regardless of the type of the input image.)
</P>
</DESCRIPTION>

